Coronavirus guidance is being updated.
Read what you can and cannot do

Palau has put measures in place to limit the spread of coronavirus (COVID-19).
For information on how to return to the UK from Palau, see Return to the UK
There is widespread disruption on international travel routes to Palau. You should check with your travel provider for updates.
Travel restrictions banning travel into Palau for travellers who have travelled from or transited through mainland China, Macao or Hong Kong in the past 14 days are in place.
Further information
See the TravelHealthPro website for further advice on travel abroad and reducing spread of respiratory viruses during the COVID-19 pandemic.
